{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 3. Installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Step 1 \u8212- Copy the RPM to your Fedora KDE machine\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Transfer the file:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\f1 win11-window-tiling-1.0.0-1.fc41kde.noarch.rpm}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Step 2 \u8212- Install with dnf\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 sudo dnf install ./win11-window-tiling-1.0.0-1.fc41kde.noarch.rpm\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Step 3 \u8212- Verify installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 rpm -q win11-window-tiling\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Expected output includes: {\f1 win11-window-tiling-1.0.0-1.fc41kde}\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 4. First-Time Setup\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Run setup\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 win11-tiling-setup\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This command:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Copies the KZones script to {\f1 ~/.local/share/kwin/scripts/}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Loads and runs KZones via KWin\u8217's scripting API\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Configures Windows 11-style Super+Arrow shortcuts in KGlobalAccel\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Log out and back in\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A fresh Plasma session ensures KWin scripts and shortcuts are fully applied.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Verify\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 win11-tiling-setup --status\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Example output:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 Edition:          Fedora KDE Plasma\line
Session type:     wayland\line
Setup status:     configured (2026-06-28T...)\line
KZones script:    installed\line
KWin:             available\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Also open {\b System Settings \u8594 ? Window Management \u8594 ? KWin Scripts} and confirm KZones is enabled.\par}
