{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 8. Troubleshooting\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Setup says \u8220"KWin not found\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 sudo dnf install plasma-workspace kwin\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Zones or shortcuts not working\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Verify the script is installed:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi0 \f1 ls ~/.local/share/kwin/scripts/kzones.kwinscript\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Re-run setup:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi0 \f1 win11-tiling-setup\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Restart KWin or log out and back in:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi0 \f1 kwin_wayland --replace &   # Wayland (use with caution)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Check {\b System Settings \u8594 ? Shortcuts} for conflicting Meta bindings.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 KZones not listed in KWin Scripts\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Re-run setup and log out/in. If still missing, load manually:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 qdbus6 org.kde.KWin /Scripting org.kde.kwin.Scripting.loadScript \\\line
  ~/.local/share/kwin/scripts/kzones.kwinscript kzones\line
qdbus6 org.kde.KWin /Scripting org.kde.kwin.Scripting.runScript kzones\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 (On older setups, use {\f1 qdbus} instead of {\f1 qdbus6}.)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Super + arrow does nothing\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Another KWin shortcut may use the same keys\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Open {\b System Settings \u8594 ? Shortcuts \u8594 ? KWin} and check {\b Window Quick Tile} entries\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Re-run {\f1 win11-tiling-setup} to restore default bindings\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Drag-to-edge snapping not working\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Confirm KZones is running in KWin Scripts\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Check zone size and activation settings in KZones configure dialog\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Ensure no other KWin script conflicts with edge detection\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Wrong edition installed\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If you installed the {\b Fedora Workstation} (GNOME) RPM by mistake, it will not work on KDE. Use the KDE edition:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\f1 win11-window-tiling-1.0.0-1.fc41kde.noarch.rpm}\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
